&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beaverton, Oregon, is a vibrant, family-friendly city&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;nestled in the heart of the picturesque Pacific Northwest. Located just seven miles west of Portland, Beaverton offers&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;the perfect balance of urban convenience and outdoor adventure&lt;/strong&gt;, making it an exceptional place to live and work. Despite being one of Oregon&#39;s largest cities, it retains a close-knit, small-town charm that residents and newcomers alike appreciate. Surrounded by lush forests, rolling hills, and stunning landscapes,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Beaverton is a gateway to outdoor activities&lt;/strong&gt;. The city is home to over&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;100 parks and 30 miles of hiking trails&lt;/strong&gt;, where you can enjoy serene walks, birdwatching, and exploring native wildlife. Whether you’re into biking, running, or simply soaking up the beauty of the Pacific Northwest, Beaverton offers countless ways to connect with nature.&lt;/p&gt;
